Staircase Climber — Count Distinct Ways to Reach the Top"

You are working as a developer for a fitness app, and you have been tasked with implementing a feature to track the number of ways a user can climb a staircase. The user can climb the stairs in steps of either 1 or 2 at a time. You need to find the total number of distinct ways the user can reach the top of the staircase, given the total number of steps.



The user is provided with the number of steps n in the staircase, and you need to calculate how many distinct ways they can climb the staircase, considering that each time they can either take 1 step or 2 steps.

Input format :
An integer n representing the number of steps in the staircase.

Output format :
An integer representing the total number of distinct ways to reach the top of the staircase.



Code constraints :
1 ≤ n ≤ 45

Sample test cases :
Input 1 :
5
Output 1 :
Total number of ways to climb 5 steps: 8

Solution:


#include<bits/stdc++.h>
using namespace std;

vector<int>dp;

int ClimbingStairs(int n){
    
    if(n == 1){
        return 1;
    }
    
    if(n == 2){
        return 2;
    }
    
    if(dp[n] != -1){
        return dp[n];
    }
    
    return dp[n] = ClimbingStairs(n-1) + ClimbingStairs(n-2);
}



int main(){
    
    int n;
    cin>>n;
    
    dp.resize(n+1,-1);
    
    cout<<ClimbingStairs(n);
}
